tip.text: The modern man cave. Come here for Ryan. He will transform you from ape to man. After your cut wash shave treatment massage, enjoy your blue moon. That's the beer they serve here.
swanky. and the cocktails are potent. go for the 'box office smash'.
cold-pressed juices. beet burger. dumplings. luscious salads. natural goodness om.
the signature salad is crunchy and fresh. spruce burger always a fail-proof option. lemonade's a perfect companion during lunch.

tip.text: the seafood undoubtedly. the crab cakes. the scallops. steak is well-marinated but not the purist steakhouse kind. did I mention you've got to order the kale salad? mindblowing. great food+ambience!
most of their pastries are above average. the apple pie was delish w/o being cloyingly sweet. the cafe latte is really good. but the tea (at $9) is daylight robbery.

tip.text: the fried chicken is amazing. and the 'gator meatballs. cocktail bluegrass and apples(?) was a delightful and deceptively strong drink. this place rocks.
the lamb ribs, oh so fine.
great for brunch and tapas for dinner!
